      <title>The singing competition</title>
      <sourceDesc>author="Nikolaeva &amp; Mayer" yearpub="2004" location="https://www.sgr.fi/yukaghir/start1.html"</sourceDesc>
      <textDesc>variety="Kolyma Yukaghir" genre="Story" daterec="1986" locrec="Unknown"</textDesc>
      <particDesc>id="008" name="Nikolaj Lixachev" age="76" gender="Male"</particDesc>
      <notes>This legend is probably influenced by Yakut mythology, as the Yakuts believed that when a good singer sings (s)he is competing with the devil's daughter. The Yukaghirs considered singing a magical action. According to traditional Yukaghir beliefs, shamans used to sing sitting on trees. Shamans often competed with one another in singing competitions.</notes>
    </fileDesc>
  </teiHeader>
